All 5 epics created and wired. Here's the summary:

## Polish Cycle 1 -- Epic Plan

Since all 4 audit reviewers crashed (producing zero findings), I conducted my own thorough assessment using 4 parallel audit agents covering UI polish, audio engine, design system, and test coverage.

### Dependency Graph

```
long-running-harness-mzn1 (Meta-Epic: UI Wiring Fix)
  └── long-running-harness-o084 [P1] QA Verification (browser evidence)
        ├── long-running-harness-k5z3 [P2] Accessibility & Motion Safety
        ├── long-running-harness-vzur [P2] Design System Consistency
        ├── long-running-harness-oeml [P2] Interaction Quality & Micro-feedback
        └── long-running-harness-t6m2 [P2] Audio Engine Robustness
```

### Key Findings That Drove the Epics

- **8 CSS files** with animations but no `prefers-reduced-motion` support
- **~30% of CSS values** bypass the token system with hardcoded pixels/colors
- **Missing loading states** in SessionBrowser, MixerPanel, RecoveryDialog
- **Silent audio failures** in synth processor (unsafe output array access)
- **Memory leaks** in decode pipeline (timeout race), effects bridge (subscription leak)
- **Negative modulo bug** in step sequencer (`-1 % 16 = -1` in JS)
- **No visual feedback** for playing notes on VirtualKeyboard, no drag zone indicators
- **Console.error calls** leaking to production users from scheduler

